Make the vinaigrette with the olive oil and red wine vinegar and leave to one side.For the steak, heat the oil and butter in a heavy-based frying pan.Cook the steak should take about five minutes (for medium) turning and colouring on both sides. When ready remove from the pan and allow to rest for a few minutes.Add the tomato quarters, olives and caperberries to the pan and quickly sauté.Deglaze the pan with the red wine and add the contents of the pan to the vinaigrette.Heat a frying pan until hot then add the olive oil and potatoes, garlic and rosemary. Sauté until golden.Wilt the spinach in a hot frying pan.Serve the steaks on top of the spinach and potatoes. Pour over a little of the vinaigrette with the tomatoes and olives.